        <div n="Y49-W112" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">H</hi>ERE <hi rend="underline">Scotus</hi> Lyes, of late as WiseAnd Learn'd as <hi rend="underline">Tom Aquinas</hi>;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-2"> Lawn Sleevs he wore, yet was no moreA Christian than <hi rend="underline">Socinus</hi>.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-3">Oaths <hi rend="underline">Pro</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Con</hi> he swallow'd down,Lov'd Gold like any Layman;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-4"> Wrote, Preach'd, and Pray'd; but yet betray'dGod's Holy-Church for <hi rend="underline">Mammon</hi>.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-5">Of e'ery Vice he had a Spice;&#13;Altho a <hi rend="underline">Rev'rend Prelate</hi>,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-6"> Yet liv'd and dy'd, if not bely'd,A true <hi rend="underline">Dissenting Zealot</hi>.</l></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-7">If such a Soul to Heav'n hath stole,&#13;And 'scap'd Old <hi rend="underline">Satan</hi>'s Clutches,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Y49-W112-line-8"> We'll then presume there may be roomFor <hi rend="underline">M</hi>──────and his D──────</l></lg></div>
